Upgrade procedure for OpenNTPD (portable)

Vendor branch : vendor/OpenBSD/openntpd   (sources live under dist/)
In-tree prefix: contrib/openntpd
Build glue     : usr.sbin/ntpd

Source: https://cdn.openbsd.org/pub/OpenBSD/OpenNTPD/openntpd-VERSION.tar.gz
        (verify against the published SHA256 / SHA256.asc in that directory)

To upgrade to a new version
---------------------------
1. Download and extract the new tarball to /tmp/openntpd-VERSION.
2. Follow the vendor-update skill (.agents/skills/vendor-update):
   - Import the pristine tree into dist/ on vendor/OpenBSD/openntpd.
   - Commit "Vendor import of openntpd VERSION" and tag
     vendor/OpenBSD/openntpd/VERSION (annotated).
3. Sync the pristine tree into contrib/openntpd (upstream src/, compat/,
   include/, m4/ layout is preserved -- do NOT flatten it).
4. Reconcile usr.sbin/ntpd/Makefile (see notes below).

Build notes (portable 6.x/7.x layout)
-------------------------------------
OpenNTPD portable no longer uses a generated config.h. The autotools build
passes feature macros (-DHAVE_*) on the command line and selects per-OS compat
objects. The in-tree bmake build in usr.sbin/ntpd reproduces this by hand:

  * ntpd and ntpctl are the SAME binary; ntpctl is installed as a hardlink and
    dispatched by argv[0]. usr.sbin/ntpd installs the ntpctl link.
  * HAVE_SENSORS is false on MidnightBSD (no sys/sensors.h) -> fake-sensors.c.
  * HAVE_LIBTLS is false (no libtls/LibreSSL in base) -> constraint-disabled.c;
    the HTTPS-constraint feature is compiled out.
  * Compat objects pulled from compat/ because base does not provide them:
    imsg.c, imsg-buffer.c (no imsg in libutil), adjfreq_freebsd.c (no adjfreq;
    uses ntp_adjtime(2)), recallocarray.c, freezero.c, plus the always-on
    socket.c, md5.c and progname.c.
    progname.c is built for get_progname(), but -DHAVE___PROGNAME keeps it from
    defining its own __progname (base libc has it).
  * Everything else (asprintf, arc4random(_uniform), closefrom, daemon,
    clock_get*, explicit_bzero, memmem, reallocarray, setproctitle, setgroups,
    setre[ug]id, setres[ug]id, strlcat, strlcpy, strtonum, sysconf) is in the
    MidnightBSD base -> passed as -DHAVE_* so the native path is used.
  * -lm is linked (isfinite); -Wno-typedef-redefinition silences the only
    warning the include/ shims produce (u_int*_t re-typedef) so the rest of the
    tree's -Werror still applies.

Verified: builds clean under -Werror and installs (ntpd + ntpctl hardlink, man
pages, ntpd.conf) on MidnightBSD 4.0.6/amd64.

When bumping the version, re-check compat/Makefile.am and configure.ac against
the base system: if MidnightBSD gains imsg in libutil, adjfreq, recallocarray
or freezero, drop the corresponding compat source and add the matching -DHAVE_*.

Local patches applied on top of upstream
-----------------------------------------
None. The historical 3.9-era MidnightBSD patches (HAVE_SENSORS guards, compat
prototypes) are obsolete -- upstream's portable layer now handles all of them.
Keep this list empty; if a local patch becomes necessary, record the upstream/
FreeBSD commit hash, affected file and re-apply context here.
